This paper deals with the evaluation of text generation models from semi-structured data, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new metric for evaluating such models, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the NLP community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for text generation and evaluation, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information extraction and database techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
